events.name: Wake Forest Demon Deacons at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Florida State kicker Roberto Aguayo kicked a career-high five field goals in a single game as the top-ranked Seminoles eased to a 43-3 victory over Wake Forest on Saturday.

video.headline: Winston Shakes Off Rust As FSU Routs Wake Forest

headlines.shortLinkText: No. 1 Noles trounce Wake

events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Bo Wallace threw for 251 yards and three touchdowns, including two in the fourth quarter, and No. 11 Mississippi rallied from a fourth-quarter deficit to stun No. 3 Alabama 23-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ole Miss stuns No. 3 Bama late

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Paul Dawson returned an interception 41 yards for a touchdown, TCU made a huge fourth-and-1 stop with just over 3 minutes left and the No. 25 Horned Frogs remained undefeated with a 37-33 victory over No. 4 Oklahoma on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: TCU knocks off No. 4 Oklahoma

events.name: LSU Tigers at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Nick Marshall passed for 207 yards, ran for 119 and accounted for four touchdowns to lead No. 5 Auburn to a 41-7 blowout of No. 15 LSU on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 5 Auburn smacks LSU in rout

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Dak Prescott threw two touchdown passes, added three Tebow-style TD runs, and No. 12 Mississippi State overwhelmed No. 6 Texas A&M 48-31 on Saturday as a new contender emerged in the SEC West.
headlines.shortLinkText: Prescott, Miss. St. rout No. 6 A&M

events.name: Baylor Bears at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Shock Linwood ran for 148 yards and the clinching touchdown and No. 7 Baylor overcame a rare off day by quarterback Bryce Petty and the nation's No. 1 offense to beat Texas 28-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Linwood lifts Baylor past Longhorns

events.name: Utah Utes at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Andy Phillips kicked a 29-yard field goal with 34 seconds left for Utah, and UCLA's Ka'imi Fairbairn missed two field-goal attempts with no time on the clock as the Utes stunned the No. 8 Bruins 30-28 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah downs No. 8 UCLA with late field goal

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Everett Golson threw a 23-yard touchdown pass to Ben Koyack in the corner of the end zone with 61 seconds left as No. 9 Notre Dame overcame two turnovers and two bungled snaps on field goal attempts on a cold, rainy Saturday to beat No. 14 Stanford 17-14.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irish edge Stanford on late TD
